He turns around and
heads towards the river

00:32:02.100 --> 00:32:04.890
as if he has forgotten about Alice.

00:32:04.890 --> 00:32:08.330
But she's tired of illusive
encounters and [inaudible] ghosts,

00:32:08.330 --> 00:32:11.550
and without a second thought,
she runs around after him.

00:32:11.550 --> 00:32:15.540
The ground around the path is not
landscaped, it is slippery, ragged,

00:32:15.540 --> 00:32:18.700
full of creepers, [inaudible],
fallen trees.

00:32:18.700 --> 00:32:23.120
Alice loses her slippers, her
flannel pajamas are torn and muddy.

00:32:23.120 --> 00:32:26.530
She scrapes her hands as she
reaches out for branches, bushes,

00:32:26.530 --> 00:32:30.250
anything that might slow her
descent toward the river.

00:32:30.250 --> 00:32:31.790
When she finally stops on the banks

00:32:31.790 --> 00:32:33.590
of the Potomac, Eric
has disappeared.

00:32:33.590 --> 00:32:39.630
She tries to catch her
breath as she looks around.

00:32:39.630 --> 00:32:43.070
The Potomac is still
recovering from a rainy season.

00:32:43.070 --> 00:32:45.870
For weeks, its impetuous
currents have carried

00:32:45.870 --> 00:32:50.250
and deposited the debris left
behind by the summer storms.

00:32:50.250 --> 00:32:53.770
Finally, in this mild beginning
of fall, the river is returning

00:32:53.770 --> 00:32:56.700
to its normal majestic course.

00:32:56.700 --> 00:33:00.830
Alice is mesmerized by the
gaze of the sun on the water.

00:33:00.830 --> 00:33:03.230
"Hi, there."

00:33:03.230 --> 00:33:06.850
Unlike Alice, Eric does
not look tired at all.

00:33:06.850 --> 00:33:11.090
He smiles at her as he sits on the
grass with his usual casual air.

00:33:11.090 --> 00:33:13.260
The expression of a
man who is not yet home

00:33:13.260 --> 00:33:16.610 position:56%
and is already planning his journey.

00:33:16.610 --> 00:33:19.650
"Long time no see," he
approaches her with a smile.

00:33:19.650 --> 00:33:22.840
"I was beginning to think
you'd never make it."

00:33:22.840 --> 00:33:24.400
She moves closer.

00:33:24.400 --> 00:33:27.060
"I'm sorry I'm late," she
thinks of telling him.

00:33:27.060 --> 00:33:28.410
"I got distracted.

00:33:28.410 --> 00:33:31.500
Half a century goes by
in the blink of an eye."

00:33:31.500 --> 00:33:33.990
"Why don't you sit down?"

00:33:33.990 --> 00:33:38.070
Alice bends over with great caution
as they taught her at the clinic,

00:33:38.070 --> 00:33:40.660
first one knee, then the other.

00:33:40.660 --> 00:33:44.540
The slipping ground is tricky
and she ends up flat on her back.

00:33:44.540 --> 00:33:46.820
She finds that she's
not uncomfortable,

00:33:46.820 --> 00:33:49.410
but will she get back on her feet?

00:33:49.410 --> 00:33:51.900
"They were all wrong, all of them.

00:33:51.900 --> 00:33:53.410
You were great.

00:33:53.410 --> 00:33:56.780
How is our little girl doing?"

00:33:56.780 --> 00:33:58.080
"She's fine.

00:33:58.080 --> 00:33:59.380
Very well actually.

00:33:59.380 --> 00:34:02.580
She's so beautiful -- our Jane
-- so confident, so grown up.

00:34:02.580 --> 00:34:04.300
We are grandparents, you know.

00:34:04.300 --> 00:34:08.010 position:56%
We have three grandchildren, and the
eldest granddaughter is pregnant.

00:34:08.010 --> 00:34:09.650
We'll be great-grandparents soon."

00:34:09.650 --> 00:34:15.430
She would like to tell him all
of that, but she hesitates.

00:34:15.430 --> 00:34:18.770
How can one tell such
things to a man in his 20s?

00:34:18.770 --> 00:34:21.980
She would not want to upset him.

00:34:21.980 --> 00:34:24.060
Eric lies down next to her.

00:34:24.060 --> 00:34:27.720
With his fingers, he
caresses the grass.

00:34:27.720 --> 00:34:31.180
Alice is beaming with light
and trembling with fear.

00:34:31.180 --> 00:34:34.530
Now he will realize
I'm old, she thinks.

00:34:34.530 --> 00:34:37.410
She's suddenly concerned
about her looks, her age,

00:34:37.410 --> 00:34:39.190
the state of her pajamas.

00:34:39.190 --> 00:34:41.660
She leans on her elbow
and lies on one side,

00:34:41.660 --> 00:34:44.340
surreptitiously checking her pants.

00:34:44.340 --> 00:34:47.030
She cannot believe what she sees.

00:34:47.030 --> 00:34:50.620
Her legs emerge from under a
miniskirt and they are firm

00:34:50.620 --> 00:34:54.510
and tanned -- the legs of a person
who has never foot in a gym,

00:34:54.510 --> 00:34:58.550
but has walked all over out
of desire and curiosity.

00:34:58.550 --> 00:35:02.130
She has not seen those legs in
a while, and bends her knee just

00:35:02.130 --> 00:35:06.710
to watch the muscle flex
under the tight, smooth skin.

00:35:06.710 --> 00:35:09.090
When she overcomes her surprise,

00:35:09.090 --> 00:35:12.620
she realizes that Eric
has gotten very close --

00:35:12.620 --> 00:35:16.640
so close, he's practically
leaning on her.

00:35:16.640 --> 00:35:20.610
Alice recognizes that unforgettable
smell of wet underbrush

00:35:20.610 --> 00:35:25.290
and saltiness, and follows his
lips as they move towards hers

00:35:25.290 --> 00:35:30.190
until they are so close
they become blurry.

00:35:30.190 --> 00:35:35.970
Kissing her with my soul upon my
lips, it suddenly took flight.

00:35:38.070 --> 00:35:40.270 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Tell us how you wrote that scene.

